            <c02 level="class">
               <did>
                  <unitid type="work">poems.lt04</unitid>
                  <unittitle type="uniform" label="Uniform Title:">
                     <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">[Alcaic Ode]</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unittitle label="First Line:">
                     <title linktype="simple">O Tu, severi relligio loci,</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate normal="1775" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1775</unitdate>
                  <langmaterial>
                     <language encodinganalog="546" langcode="lat">Latin</language>
                  </langmaterial>
               </did>
               <bibliography>
                  <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#S/H_1966"
                          linktype="simple">Starr/Hendrickson (eds.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Complete Poems</title> (1966),  151-152 (with English
							prose	translation)</bibref>
                  <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#LoR_1969"
                          linktype="simple">Lonsdale (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poems</title> (1969),  317-318 (with English
							prose	translation)</bibref>
               </bibliography>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>
                     <persname normal="Gray, Thomas, 1716-1771">Gray</persname> wrote this
							poem in the album of the monastery of the Grande Chartreuse on this
							second visit on <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1741"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="17410821" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">21 August 1741</date>
                     </extref>, during
							his journey from <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glplaces.shtml#Turin (Torino province, Piedmont, Italy),         inhabited place [7005688]"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <geogname normal="Turin (Torino province, Piedmont, Italy), inhabited place          [7005688]">Turin</geogname>
                     </extref> to <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glplaces.shtml#Lyon (Rhône, Rhône-Alpes,            France), inhabited place [7008772]"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <geogname normal="Lyon (Rhône, Rhône-Alpes, France), inhabited place            [7008772]">Lyon</geogname>
                     </extref>, when he was returning 
							alone from the Grand Tour. 
							First published, as <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Ode</title>, in
								<extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Mason, William, 1724-1797"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Mason, William,          1724-1797">Mason</persname>'s</extref>
                     <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Memoirs</title> (<date normal="1775" type="publication" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1775</date>), <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=primary&amp;edition=1775&amp;part=1&amp;page=117"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">117-118</extref>. MS translation into English by <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Wharton, Thomas, 1717-1794"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Wharton, Thomas, 1717-1794">Thomas
									Wharton</persname>
                     </extref>.
						</p>
               </scopecontent>
